        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Well, I was testing the affliction focus items a bit, and I found something very odd.  I will give my findings about the focus item in a bit, but this struck me as odd...</P><P><b>Pyrocruor</b><BR>DoT for 1998 Hit Points (HP) in 18 ticks</P><P>Thats the description of Pyrocruor in the spdat.  I casted it on myself, and this is what happened, three times.  This is without any DoT focus item equipped:</P><P>Initial HP:  2923<BR>Tick #    HP<BR>1         2847<BR>2         2771<BR>3         2695<BR>4         2619<BR>5         2543<BR>6         2467<BR>7         2391<BR>8         2315<BR>9         2239<BR>10        2163<BR>11        2087<BR>12        2011<BR>13        1935<BR>14        1859<BR>15        1783<BR>16        1707<BR>17        1631<BR>18        1555<BR>19        1479</P><P>Tot. DMG: 1426</P><P>The first odd thing you'll notice is that there are 19 ticks of damage there.  It should have been 18.  Again, I did not have my Extended Affliction III item equipped (it was in a backpack) and I did not get a Your Bone-Clasped Girdle begins to sparkle message, meaning its a normal cast.  Why there were 19 ticks, I have no idea.</P><P>Secondly, the damage is unusually high.  Once you factor in my standing HP regen (7 hp/tick) and the PvP damage reduction, you get this:</P><P>Total HP Lost:  1426<BR>HP Regen:       1559 [1426 + (7*19)]<BR>PvP:            2362 [1559 / 0.66]</P><P>This means Pyrocruor does 2362 damage over 1 minute 54 seconds instead of 1998 damage over 1 minute 48 seconds as the SPDat says?  That puts Pyrocruor at about 21 dps, over the 18.5 dps that we thought it was.  That also gives it a 5.905 damage per mana rating, significantly better than the 4.995 damage per mana rating the spdat says it is.</P><P>Something must be up.  Anyone see any flaws here or is that dot better than we think it is?  I saw something similar in Splurt as well, and those are the only two I've tested so far.  So, before I continue, figure out whats wrong here...</P><P>Daedrea Darksoul</font></td>
